{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "06", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "19", "M": "18", "S": "22"}}, "news": [{"title": "Mahindra Lifespaces and Sattva Group launch residential projects in Mumbai", "para": "Mahindra Lifespace Developers has launched Mahindra BeaconHill, a 58-storey residential project in Mahalaxmi, South Mumbai, with a potential GDV of \u20b91,650 crore. In a separate development, Sattva Group has introduced Sattva Sumera, its first Mumbai residential project, a \u20b95,500 crore development featuring twin towers with over 20 lakh sq ft of space.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/mahindra-lifespaces-and-sattva-group-unveil-major-residential-projects-in-mumbai/130861881?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-54028/130861881.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Brigade Enterprises' net profit rises by 6.51% to \u20b9724.76 crore in FY26", "para": "Brigade Enterprises announced a 6.51 percent rise in its net profit for the financial year 2025-26. The company's profit after tax reached \u20b9724.76 crore. Total income also grew by 11.21 percent. The board recommended a dividend and approved a bonus share issue. Real estate sales and leasing business showed strong performance. The hospitality segment also reported revenue growth.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/brigade-enterprises-reports-651-increase-in-net-profit-for-fy26/130861660?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-52966/130861660.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "NOC for constructions near defence establishments cannot be insisted belatedly: Bombay HC", "para": "The Bombay High Court declared that late demands for No Objection Certificates regarding construction adjacent to defense facilities are not permissible. The court mandated that authorities grant occupancy certificates for two residential buildings located near INS Trata. It emphasized that any security issues must be identified and resolved at the outset of construction.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/noc-for-constructions-near-defence-establishments-cannot-be-insisted-belatedly-bombay-hc/130857222?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-344912/130857222.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Shree Cement net profit rises by 55.60% to \u20b91,748.66 crore in FY26", "para": "Shree Cement announced a significant 55.60% rise in net profit for FY26, reaching \u20b91,748.66 crore. Total income also saw an 8.72% increase. The company's cement sales volume grew by 11% year-on-year. The company is expanding its ready-mix concrete business and commissioned a new integrated plant in Karnataka. The board recommended a dividend of \u20b970 per equity share.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/shree-cement-net-profit-rises-by-55-60-to-1748-66-crore-in-fy26/130856516?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-41980/130856516.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}, {"title": "Alpha Corp Development acquires Earth Infrastructures' two stalled projects", "para": "Alpha Corp Development has acquired three stalled projects of Earth Infrastructures through an NCLT resolution process, offering relief to over 3,000 homebuyers. The Supreme Court's intervention restored Alpha Corp's resolution plan, directing GNIDA to waive penal interest and mandating Alpha to clear dues over 24 months without burdening buyers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/alpha-corp-development-secures-acquisition-of-earth-infrastructures-stalled-projects/130861281?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-45726/130861281.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit dips by 48.09% to \u20b9575.84 crore in FY26", "para": "Kansai Nerolac Paints (KNPL) reported a significant 48.09% drop in net consolidated profit for FY26, reaching \u20b9575.84 crore. Despite a 2.96% rise in total income to \u20b98,197.85 crore, the company cited rising raw material costs and rupee depreciation as key factors. The board recommended a 250% dividend for FY26.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/paints/kansai-nerolac-paints-reports-48-net-profit-decline-announces-dividend-changes/130856152?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22374/130856152.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "paints"}, {"title": "Aditya Birla Real Estate posts net loss of \u20b9114.82 crore in FY26", "para": "Aditya Birla Real Estate reported a net consolidated loss of \u20b9114.82 crore for FY26, a reduction from the previous year's \u20b9157.44 crore loss. Despite a significant drop in total income, the company's Q4 FY26 saw a profit of \u20b95.39 crore. The board recommended a 25% dividend for FY26.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/aditya-birla-real-estate-reports-11482-crore-loss-in-fy26-sees-revenue-decline/130855686?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-115119/130855686.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Embassy Developments shares resume normal trading after NCLAT quashes insolvency proceedings", "para": "Embassy Developments\u2019 shares have resumed normal trading on stock exchanges after the NCLAT set aside insolvency proceedings against the company. The firm has also exited the ASM framework. It reported strong pre-sales growth in FY26, indicating steady business performance.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/embassy-developments-exits-insolvency-normal-trading-resumes-on-bse-and-nse/130851553?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-68160/130851553.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Gujarat: Bail denied to Popular Builders owner in land forgery case", "para": "A sessions court denied bail to 67-year-old Popular Builders owner Dashrath Patel in a 2022 land fraud case. Patel is accused of conspiring to forge land records for a 1983 sale deed. The court cited the seriousness of the offense, Patel's role, past conduct, and ongoing investigation in its decision.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/gujarat-builder-dashrath-patel-denied-bail-in-land-fraud-case/130847749?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26460/130847749.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Pune district administration to reclaim 15 plots for lease breaches", "para": "Pune district has identified 240 violations on government land leased long-term, leading to reclamation orders for 15 parcels.  These breaches include non-renewal, land use changes, and unauthorized constructions. The administration is taking action after a comprehensive survey and hearings, following recommendations from the Vikas Kharge committee.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/pune-district-administration-actively-reclaims-leased-lands-due-to-violations/130847779?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-50978/130847779.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Scrutiny on building sites using potable water in DLF phases in Gurugram", "para": "DLF City phases are witnessing a crackdown on illegal potable water extraction at construction sites, with motors removed from seven locations. Officials are urging fines and emphasizing the need for non-potable sources to ensure residents receive uninterrupted water supply amidst rising urban demand and declining groundwater levels.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/gurugram-cracks-down-on-illegal-potable-water-use-at-construction-sites/130842858?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-84552/130842858.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Odisha RERA allows hard copy submission for offline registered projects", "para": "The Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) has revised its quarterly progress report formats for builders, allowing hard-copy submissions for offline-registered projects. These changes, effective from June 2026, aim to enhance transparency and compliance by making disclosures outcome-oriented and capturing detailed project advancement beyond basic construction.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/odisha-rera-introduces-hard-copy-qpr-submission-for-improved-project-transparency/130842688?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-40164/130842688.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}, {"title": "Noida: Consumer forum directs Ajnara India to pay \u20b91.7 lakh for failing to handover flat", "para": "A Noida consumer commission has ordered real estate developer Ajnara India Ltd to pay Rs 1.71 lakh with 6% interest to a customer. The developer failed to deliver a flat booked in 2018 or refund the booking amount. The commission also awarded Rs 4,000 for litigation costs and mental agony.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/noida-consumer-forum-orders-ajnara-india-to-pay-17-lakh-for-unfulfilled-flat-purchase/130842646?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-34500/130842646.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Raymond Realty posts net profit of \u20b9304.59 crore in FY26", "para": "Raymond Realty achieved a net consolidated profit of \u20b9304.59 crore in the financial year 2025-26. The company's total income reached \u20b93,039.42 crore. Pre-sales in the final quarter were \u20b91,519 crore. The board recommended a 20 percent dividend. Booking value grew 31% year-on-year to \u20b93,023 crore. The total portfolio stands at \u20b942,000 crore GDV.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/raymond-realty-posts-net-profit-of-304-59-crore-in-fy26/130830340?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-40670/130830340.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Bagmane Prime Office REIT IPO subscribed 71% on day 1", "para": "Blackstone-backed Bagmane Prime Office REIT's IPO saw 71% subscription on its first day, attracting bids for 10.55 crore units. The Rs 3,405-crore issue, with a price band of Rs 95-100, aims to acquire office assets in Bengaluru. The REIT's portfolio comprises six premium business parks.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/bagmane-prime-office-reit-ipo-launches-with-71-subscription-on-day-1/130830418?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-293931/130830418.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Aadhar Housing Finance's net profit rises by 20.18% to \u20b91,095.88 crore in FY26", "para": "Aadhar Housing Finance achieved a significant 20.18 percent growth in its net consolidated profit for the financial year 2025-26. The company's profit after tax reached \u20b91,095.88 crore. Total income also saw a healthy increase of 18.59 percent. Aadhar Housing Finance crossed the \u20b930,000 crore AUM milestone.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/housing-finance/aadhar-housing-finances-net-profit-rises-by-20-18-to-1095-88-crore-in-fy26/130828253?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-83922/130828253.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "housing-finance"}]}